    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chinese painting technique using meticulous brush work with attention to details, forms and standards. Usually confined to color paintings. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049849/March, Some Technical Terms of Chinese Painting (1935)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種中國繪畫技法，以精細的筆觸，注重畫作細節、格局與規矩，常用於彩畫。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chinese schildertechniek met een minutieus penseelwerk, met veel oog voor details, vormen en standaarden. Meestal beperkt tot schilderijen in kleur. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
